Words 1601-1700

  1. matching
    The matching colors on her dress and shoes looked perfect.

  2. material
    The material used for the table is strong and durable.

  3. mathematics
    She enjoys studying mathematics at school.

  4. maths
    Maths is her favorite subject in class.

  5. matter
    This is a serious matter that needs attention.

  6. maximum
    The maximum speed allowed here is 60 miles per hour.

  7. May
    May is the fifth month of the year.

  8. may
    You may leave early if you finish your work.

  9. maybe
    Maybe we can go to the park later.

  10. me
    Can you help me with this problem?

  11. meal
    We had a delicious meal at the restaurant.

  12. mean
    What does this word mean in the sentence?

  13. meaning
    The meaning of the story became clear at the end.

  14. means
    They used every means possible to solve the issue.

  15. meanwhile
    Meanwhile, she waited patiently for the bus.

  16. measure
    We need to measure the length of the table.

  17. measurement
    The measurement of the room is 10 feet by 12 feet.

  18. meat
    He bought some fresh meat from the market.

  19. media
    The news was shared widely on social media.

  20. medical
    She went to the hospital for medical advice.

  21. medicine
    The doctor gave her medicine for her cold.

  22. medium
    She ordered a medium-sized coffee.

  23. meet
    Let’s meet at the park after school.

  24. meeting
    The meeting will start at 10 a.m. sharp.

  25. melt
    The ice will melt if you leave it in the sun.

  26. member
    He is a member of the local sports club.

  27. memory
    She has a good memory for names and faces.

  28. mental
    Mental health is just as important as physical health.

  29. mention
    Did she mention the time of the event?

  30. menu
    The menu has a variety of dishes to choose from.

  31. mess
    The room was in a mess after the party.

  32. message
    I left a message for you on the table.

  33. metal
    The gate is made of strong metal.

  34. method
    This method is the easiest way to solve the problem.

  35. metre
    The table is two metres long.

  36. middle
    He stood in the middle of the room.

  37. midnight
    She stayed awake until midnight to finish her work.

  38. might
    He might come to the party later.

  39. mild
    The weather today is mild and pleasant.

  40. mile
    The nearest town is five miles away.

  41. military
    He served in the military for ten years.

  42. milk
    She drinks a glass of milk every morning.

  43. million
    The company made a profit of one million dollars.

  44. mind
    Please keep in mind the rules of the game.

  45. mine
    This book is mine, not yours.

  46. mineral
    Water contains important minerals for the body.

  47. minimum
    The minimum age to drive is 18 years old.

  48. minister
    The minister gave a speech about education.

  49. minor
    There was a minor mistake in the report.

  50. minority
    A small minority of people disagreed with the decision.

  51. minute1
    Please wait for a minute while I check.

  52. mirror
    She looked at herself in the mirror before leaving.

  53. miss
    I miss my friends when they are away.

  54. missing
    The missing keys were found under the sofa.

  55. mission
    Their mission is to help people in need.

  56. mistake
    I made a mistake in my calculations.

  57. mix
    Mix the flour and water to make the dough.

  58. mixed
    The salad was made with mixed vegetables.

  59. mixture
    The cake is a mixture of flour, sugar, and eggs.

  60. mobile
    She bought a new mobile phone last week.

  61. model
    The car model is very popular this year.

  62. modern
    The building has a modern design.

  63. modify
    We need to modify the plan to make it better.

  64. moment
    Please wait a moment while I finish this.

  65. Monday
    The meeting is scheduled for next Monday.

  66. money
    He saved money to buy a new bike.

  67. monitor
    The teacher will monitor the students during the test.

  68. monkey
    The monkey climbed the tree to get a banana.

  69. month
    She will visit her family next month.

  70. mood
    He is in a good mood today.

  71. moon
    The moon was bright and full last night.

  72. moral
    The story teaches a moral lesson about honesty.

  73. more
    Can I have more water, please?

  74. morning
    She goes for a run every morning.

  75. most
    Most people enjoy sunny weather.

  76. mostly
    The work is mostly finished now.

  77. mother
    Her mother is a kind and caring person.

  78. motor
    The motor of the car needs to be repaired.

  79. motorcycle
    He rides a motorcycle to work every day.

  80. mount
    They plan to mount the TV on the wall.

  81. mountain
    We climbed the mountain during our vacation.

  82. mouse
    The mouse ran across the kitchen floor.

  83. mouth
    She opened her mouth to speak.

  84. move
    Please move the chair closer to the table.

  85. movement
    The movement of the train was smooth and fast.

  86. movie
    We watched a great movie last night.

  87. much
    Thank you very much for your help.

  88. mud
    The children played in the mud after the rain.

  89. multiple
    The problem has multiple solutions to consider.

  90. multiply
    If you multiply five by two, you get ten.

  91. mum
    My mum makes the best cookies.

  92. murder
    The detective solved the murder case quickly.

  93. muscle
    Regular exercise helps to build muscle strength.

  94. museum
    We visited the art museum on our trip.

  95. music
    She loves listening to classical music.

  96. musical
    The musical performance was amazing.

  97. musician
    He is a talented musician who plays the guitar.

  98. must
    You must wear a helmet while riding a bike.

  99. my
    My bag is on the chair near the door.

  100. myself
    I made this cake all by myself.
